{"word":"H5006 - נָאַץ - nâʼats - naw-ats' - Abhor","slug":"H5006","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">נָאַץ</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>nâʼats"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>naw-ats'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Abhor"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E0;&#x05D0;&#x05E5; - na&#x0302;'ats</b> - <i>naw-ats'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>scorn</i>; or (<a href='B:250 12:5'>Ecc 12:5</a>) by interchange for <a href=\"#/H5132\">H5132</a>, to <i>bloom: - </i>abhor, (give occasion to) blaspheme, contemn, despise, flourish, X great, provoke."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H5007\">H5007</a>"}]}